pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$background"
elements:
  - elementId: top-bar
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [0, 0, 1280, 6]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"
  - elementId: title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 18, 1100, 38]
    content:
      style: "$actionTitle"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>ROAS Declines 35–55% When Budget Doubles, Confirming Universal Saturation</p>
  - elementId: divider
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [60, 58, 1160, 1]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$border"
  - elementId: roas-chart
    elementType: chart
    bounds: [60, 72, 780, 300]
    type: bar
    data:
      - {grain: "Bing Ads", baseline: 6.27, doubled: 3.99}
      - {grain: "Google Ads", baseline: 4.03, doubled: 2.51}
      - {grain: "Meta Ads", baseline: 5.02, doubled: 3.35}
      - {grain: "Search", baseline: 10.33, doubled: 5.79}
      - {grain: "Remarketing DPA", baseline: 9.71, doubled: 6.44}
      - {grain: "Remarketing Brand", baseline: 7.13, doubled: 5.65}
    x: grain
    y: [baseline, doubled]
    names: ["Baseline (1.0x)", "Doubled (2.0x)"]
    colors: ["$primary", "$accent"]
    legend: {position: bottom, fontSize: 12}
    yAxis:
      title: "ROAS"
      gridLine: {color: "$grid"}
      min: 0
    xAxis:
      label: {fontSize: 11}
    dataLabels:
      show: true
      fontSize: 11
  - elementId: right-insight
    elementType: text
    bounds: [880, 72, 340, 300]
    content:
      fontSize: 15
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Key Findings:</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:6px">• <strong>Search</strong> has the largest absolute decline (-4.54x, -44%) due to its high starting ROAS.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:6px">• <strong>Remarketing Brand</strong> shows the smallest decline (-1.48x, -21%), suggesting more linear scaling.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:6px">• All spend-enabled channels show ROAS decline, confirming universal saturation.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:6px">• <strong>Google Ads</strong> and <strong>Meta Ads</strong> decline 33-38%, consistent with their Hill-function fits.</p>
  - elementId: bottom-table
    elementType: table
    bounds: [60, 390, 1160, 200]
    columnWidths: [0.22, 0.15, 0.15, 0.18, 0.15, 0.15]
    rowHeights: [0.14, 0.14, 0.14, 0.14, 0.14, 0.14, 0.16]
    style: "$default"
    rows:
      - - content: {text: "Grain"}
        - content: {text: "Baseline"}
        - content: {text: "2.0x ROAS"}
        - content: {text: "Absolute Decline"}
        - content: {text: "% Decline"}
        - content: {text: "Fit R²"}
      - - content: {text: "Search"}
        - content: {text: "10.33x"}
        - content: {text: "5.79x"}
        - content: {text: "-4.54x"}
        - content: {text: "-44%"}
        - content: {text: "0.750"}
      - - content: {text: "Remarketing DPA"}
        - content: {text: "9.71x"}
        - content: {text: "6.44x"}
        - content: {text: "-3.27x"}
        - content: {text: "-34%"}
        - content: {text: "0.682"}
      - - content: {text: "Remarketing Brand"}
        - content: {text: "7.13x"}
        - content: {text: "5.65x"}
        - content: {text: "-1.48x"}
        - content: {text: "-21%"}
        - content: {text: "0.304"}
      - - content: {text: "Meta Ads"}
        - content: {text: "5.02x"}
        - content: {text: "3.35x"}
        - content: {text: "-1.67x"}
        - content: {text: "-33%"}
        - content: {text: "0.680"}
      - - content: {text: "Google Ads"}
        - content: {text: "4.03x"}
        - content: {text: "2.51x"}
        - content: {text: "-1.52x"}
        - content: {text: "-38%"}
        - content: {text: "0.845"}
      - - content: {text: "Bing Ads"}
        - content: {text: "6.27x"}
        - content: {text: "3.99x"}
        - content: {text: "-2.28x"}
        - content: {text: "-36%"}
        - content: {text: "0.266"}
  - elementId: bottom-insight
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 605, 1160, 80]
    content:
      fontSize: 15
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>Implication:</strong> No channel escapes diminishing returns. The optimal budget allocation is not at 2.0x for any channel. Portfolio-level ROAS optimization requires moving spend from high-saturation, low-marginal-ROAS channels (Pmax, Google 90d) to high-ROAS, underfunded channels (Search, Bing Ads).</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Stage 5 Budget Simulation, Key Budget Insights</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>09</p>
